The paper deals with the problem of finding a minimum power Steiner tree, which is a problem commonly encountered in wireless network design. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of LP relaxation and randomized rounding, which are common techniques in the field of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem of finding a Steiner tree is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG) and the paper also involves a decomposition theorem, which is a common tool in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of approximation algorithms, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
